abstract: ATLANTA Feb. 4.--The Rev. F.L. Dupont, hailing from Farmington or Hopkinsville, Ky., was carried to the station-house here last night supposed to be intoxicated. He says the cause of his strange conduct is to let his wife get the insurance on his life.

abstract: WASHINGTON, Feb. 19.--An anti-polygamy meeting of the Protestant churches of Washington, under the auspices of the Pastors' Union, was held in the Memorial Church in this city this afternoon.
